value.title: Elizabeth Warren backs Newsom in recall fight, accuses 'Trump Republicans' of 'coming to grab power'
value.excerpt: California Gov. Gavin Newsom received the backing of Sen. Elizabeth Warren in a fiery ad released Wednesday by the top progressive who accused “Trump Republicans” of “coming to grab power in California.”

value.title: Biden raises eyebrows with claim he 'used to drive' 18-wheeler truck
value.excerpt: Biden was visiting a Mack Truck facility when he made the claim to have driven the massive trucks before, which require a special kind of license to drive.

value.title: Biden confuses Trump with Obama, calls it 'Freudian slip'
value.excerpt: President Biden mixed up former President Obama and former President Trump during a speech Wednesday in what he referred to as a "Freudian slip."

value.title: McAuliffe attacks Youngkin by tying him to Trump's election lies
value.excerpt: Virginia's Terry McAuliffe, in an effort to tie his gubernatorial opponent, Glenn Youngkin, to all things Donald Trump, is now linking the Republican nominee to the former President's top focus: so-called election integrity.

value.title: US, Russia hold 'substantive' strategic stability talks as Moscow raps Biden for comments
value.excerpt: US and Russian officials had "professional and substantive talks" on strategic stability in Switzerland, the State Department said in a statement Wednesday.

value.title: 'Unfairly penalized': Residents, senators in northern border states question Biden's border closure
value.excerpt: With Canada's vaccination rates higher now than in US, some are wondering if continued closure is more about the southern border than northern one.

value.title: Brandi Love Wants Ron DeSantis To Run in 2024 if Donald Trump Doesn't
value.excerpt: "Even I can admit that Donald Trump has an obnoxious arrogance about him that rubs some people the wrong way," the adult film actress told Newsweek.

value.title: New York Times reporter deletes tweet calling Trump supporters ‘enemies of the state’
value.excerpt: A New York Times reporter deleted a tweet that called supporters of former President Trump “enemies of the state,” following a viral blowback online.

value.title: Biden: If U.S. has 'real shooting war' it could be result of cyber attacks
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Tuesday warned that if the United States ended up in a "real shooting war" with a "major power" it could be the result of a significant cyber attack on the country, highlighting what Washington sees as growing threats posed by Russia and China.

value.title: New Jersey town drops case against ‘F--- Biden’ sign lady after ACLU intervenes: report
value.excerpt: A town in New Jersey has decided to end its effort to have a resident remove various anti-Biden signs from her property, including several that contain profanity.

value.title: Trump vows ‘we won’t mask our children’ in wake of new CDC recommendation
value.excerpt: Donald Trump blasted the Biden administration after the CDC recommended indoor mask mandates in most areas of the US as well as in all K-12 schools, regardless of vaccination status.

value.title: Texas voters brush aside Trump endorsement and name Jake Ellzey the winner in a House special election in Texas
value.excerpt: The vacancy stemmed from the February death of Rep. Ron Wright, whose widow Susan was endorsed by Trump but who has lagged in fundraising and campaigning.

value.title: America First Legal demands info on Biden's 'extreme' open border policies: 'The rails have been ripped off'
value.excerpt: America First Legal (AFL), former Trump adviser Stephen Miller's legal group, filed Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) requests with several executive branch agencies in an attempt to obtain records and data on Biden administration's "extreme" open border policies.

value.title: Biden considering vaccine mandate for federal workers, says unvaccinated not as 'smart' as he thought
value.excerpt: President Biden said Tuesday he is considering requiring all federal employees to be vaccinated and questioned the intelligence of those that have yet to do so.

value.title: Cops blame Trump, Republicans for allegedly inspiring and then downplaying Jan. 6 Capitol attack
value.excerpt: Four police officers who defended the Capitol from the pro-Trump mob that invaded it on Jan. 6 criticized the former president and Republicans who are loyal to him for allegedly inspiring then downplaying the attack, asking members of the select committee investigating Jan. 6 to get to the bottom of

value.title: Biden: Masking Again 'Another Step on Our Journey to Defeating This Virus'
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden is defending updated CDC guidelines that say even people who have been vaccinated against COVID-19 should wear masks in some places.

value.title: Trump, lawmakers honor Sen. Mike Enzi after sudden death from bike accident
value.excerpt: From former President Donald Trump to Rep. Liz Cheney to Sen. Tim Kaine, many on both sides of the aisle remembered the life and accomplishments of Senator Mike Enzi.

value.title: Buttigieg to visit Port of Baltimore to tout Biden’s infrastructure deal Thursday
value.excerpt: U.S. Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg will visit the Port of Baltimore Thursday to tout the benefits of President Biden’s bipartisan infrastructure deal.

value.title: Trump officials can testify to Congress about his role in Capitol attack, DoJ says
value.excerpt: Move declines to assert executive privilege for then acting attorney general Jeffrey Rosen, clearing path for others to testify

value.title: Harris calls on Black lawyers to fight states’ voter-integrity laws
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris urged Black lawyers Tuesday to challenge new election laws in mostly Republican-led states that she said are intended to restrict minority voting and shift vote-counting to partisan entities.

value.title: Biden wants Putin to behave. So why not go after his money?
value.excerpt: Kremlin critics say the U.S. president needs to do more than take incremental measures. But insiders warn that aiming for Putin’s pocketbook could be dangerous.

value.title: Barrasso grills Haaland on Biden's BLM nominee, tree-spiking during hearing
value.excerpt: Barrasso pursued his line of questioning during a Tuesday committee hearing on the president’s Department of Interior budget request.

value.title: Officer: Trump 'helped create this monstrosity'
value.excerpt: In testimony before the panel probing the attack on the U.S. Capitol, a police sergeant blasted former President Donald Trump's description of the scene as "a loving crowd". (July 27)

value.title: DOJ tells former Trump officials they can testify about efforts to overturn election
value.excerpt: Jeffrey Rosen, who was acting attorney general after William Barr stepped down, is among the officials being allowed to testify.

value.title: Joe Biden's 'Where's Mom?' Remarks Go Viral as Critics Jump on Apparent Confusion
value.excerpt: The president called Representative Jim Langevin "Paul" at an event celebrating the Americans with Disabilities Act.
